<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - PROSTAR&#8482; - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - TILT-AWAY BUMPER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>TILT-AWAY BUMPER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The two chassis hinge brackets are designed to aid the mechanic during removal and installation of the
                tilt-away bumper. The outside holes of the chassis hinge brackets are notched to allow the mount bolts
                to be partially removed from the tilt-away bumper mount hinges. Then, the tilt-away bumper can be
                removed from the chassis mount hinge brackets.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tilt-Away Bumper - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release latches and lower the tilt-away bumper.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If equipped with fog lights, disconnect electrical connectors from fog lights.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901101.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Bumper Hinge Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNT NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PINS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUMPER HINGE BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CHASSIS HINGE BRACKETS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two pins and mount nuts from two bumper hinge bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901102.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Support Cable</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BUMPER HINGE BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHASSIS HINGE BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SUPPORT CABLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CLEVIS PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. CLEVIS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide two bumper hinge bolts out of two chassis hinge brackets far enough to clear the
                    inside of the chassis hinge brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clevis pin from each clevis and disconnect two support cables.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901103" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901103.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Tilt-Away Bumper</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CHASSIS HINGE BRACKETS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TILT-AWAY BUMPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BUMPER HINGE BRACKETS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. NYLON BUSHINGS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the aid of an assistant, remove the tilt-away bumper from the chassis hinge
                    brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If replacing nylon bushings, remove them from the bumper hinge brackets.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Tilt-Away Bumper - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If replacing nylon bushings, insert new bushings into the bumper hinge brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901103">Figure 4, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two bumper hinge bolts into the bumper hinge brackets, making sure that the bolt
                    heads are on the outside of the hinge brackets and the ends of the bolts are not protruding through
                    the hinge brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901103">Figure 4, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the aid of an assistant, install the tilt-away bumper on the chassis hinge brackets
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901103">Figure 4, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slightly lift each side of the tilt-away bumper to slide the mount bolts completely
                    through the chassis hinge brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect two support cables to the tilt-away bumper with a clevis and clevis pin on each
                    side (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901102">Figure 3, Items 3, 4, and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two locknuts on two bumper hinge bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901101">Figure 2, Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 12 to 15 lbf-ft (16 to
                    20 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two pins through holes in two hinge bracket bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901101">Figure 2, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If equipped with fog lights, connect electrical connector to fog lights.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the tilt-away bumper and secure latches.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
